7,http://www.armslist.com/posts/495007,For Sale:  Very Early Winchester 1892 (circa 1893),"Midwest City, Oklahoma City, Oklahoma",$ 600,"Listed On: Tuesday, July 31, 2012",Rifles,Winchester                                                                                ,32-20 Winchester                                                                                ,Lever Action                                                                                ,Rifle,"Winchester 1892 in .32-20 Winchester (.32 WCF).  This is rifle is from the second year of production.  Serial number shows a manufacture date of 1893, or 119 years ago!

Metal has a nice patina on it.  Has normal wear that one would expect an 120 year rifle to have.  But nothing major.  The wood is really nice, most likely refinished, but who ever did it did a good good.  Definitely a linseed oil finish.  Action is still smooth and the lock-up is tight.  Octagon barrel, and the hammer has the more desired widow's peak checkering on it.  Bore is dark, but not pitted.  The rifling is still strong.  I'm sure this rifle could tell some stories!
Serial number 350XX
I'm pricing this rifle to sell!"

32,http://www.armslist.com/posts/495032,For Sale/Trade:  Glock 30 SF,"Starke County, South Bend, Indiana",$ 550,"Listed On: Friday, August 3, 2012",Handguns,Glock                                                                                ,45 ACP                                                                                ,Striker Fire                                                                                ,Pistol,"I have a Glock 30 SF up for sale.
The empty shell case is from 3/16/12.
I bought it new unfired. I have put no more than 100 round through it and it shoots great. I have just decided to move to a G19.
The 30 comes with everything you get when you buy new plus 2 installed Pierce magazine floor plates, the original Glock floor plates, a Pierce grip plug, and a Foxx IWB RH tuckable holster.

The Pierce floor plates do not add any capacity or length, just a similar texture as the rest of the grip for the pinky. The sights are standard white U rear and dot front. The Foxx holster from what I can tell is similar to the crossbreed. The only thing I would mention is that the 30 is not super snug in the holster by itself. When worn no problems at all.
I'm asking $550 for everything.
I would consider a trades for a similarly outfitted Gen4 G26 or 19, or 9mm ammo + cash.
I will need to see a IDL and a LTC. I am near Knox and work in Michigan City and willing to drive a reasonable distance.
Thanks for looking and pm me with any questions."
